review_blob: Nice color, great aroma of raspberries of course, (bottle) taste was a definitive raspberry some nut and chocolate hints after you get past the fruit. Mostly smooth.

Go out of my way to get this in a bottle in SoCal. This beer holds a soft spot for me as its from home... Nice color, not too dark. Sweet aroma, some fruit, chocolates. Smooth nutty flavor with a little bit obite.
Red in color, not too pink nor dark. Frothy on pour. Sweet cherry aroma. Tart cherry taste. Medium body. No aftertaste. Nice fruity beer, reasonably priced for a specialty.

Pretty reddish color, tart cherry but skunky aroma. Flavor is tart, cherries at beginning, but musty, harsh finish. I really disliked this beer, but am wondering if I had a bad bottle from our local wine shop... May give it another try, but really steep price may deter that.

Deeeeelicious!! The flavor was so smooth, excellent scent of sweet cherries, not too sweet on the palate tho. Nice smooth finish, not bitter, no after-taste. High alcohol, but you cannot taste it at all. Dangerous :-)
